<br>
Fear-kiting is awesome and the two pets make mincemeat out of anything in an outdoor zone. I buff everything, SoW everything, Necro casts darkness, another DoT if needed, fear, we sic the two pets on it and I whack away from behind. There is virtually no downtime as I use minimal mana (occasional FoL and some buffing) and the Necro uses his life to mana spell and taps. If all goes well nobody takes any damage, or only a couple hits.<br>
<br>
Add in the fact that it is very tough to kill a Necromancer (they are the best caster for escaping death, without teleporting to another zone at least. These guys just do not die with feign death, harmshield, taps, fear, darkness, and pets) and a Beastlord so there is little chance of being killed as long as you do not really mess up a pull.<br>
<br>
Any classes that can use spells do very well with a Beastlord though. I prefer to not fight with a pure meleer (maybe Monks are alright) because they are too one-dimensional, which  really limits what one can do. Warriors pull a lot of aggro and end up having to be healed too often for my taste. Rogues are alright if they can get enough backstabs in. Monks are pretty good with mend and nice melee skills. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uknomraski.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knomraski</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast Prince</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/6/02 10:10:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theunholytrinity.org/cracks_smileys/contrib/constrector/cheesess.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Your favorite class to duo with is:</span><hr size=1> I'd say my favorite duo partner is a monk, or maybe another beastlord.  We partner well with almost anyone though. <p><img src=http://www.emerald-guardians.com/characters/steenky.gif>
